In a '''Transmogrified Junction''' the entrances from north and south are located on one level together with the exits to east and west. On the other level the exits to north and south are located together with the entrances from east and west.

The junction require OpenTTD version  

==Pros==
* Quite fast.
* Quite compact.
* Traffic jams are unlikely since tracks split before they merge.
* No loops.

==Cons==
* There are slopes on the straight tracks and on at least half the turning tracks.

